00:20:45.690 --> 00:20:48.830
Yes, absolutely.

00:20:48.830 --> 00:20:51.570
So first of all, I'm
really easy on myself.

00:20:51.570 --> 00:20:55.520
As a -- in the sense that we just
knew we were going to drop balls.

00:20:55.520 --> 00:20:57.210
We told our sons early on.

00:20:57.210 --> 00:21:00.790
Like, we are not going to
remember to get this form in.

00:21:00.790 --> 00:21:03.470
We are not going to
be the class parents.

00:21:03.470 --> 00:21:05.270
We're just not.

00:21:05.270 --> 00:21:11.250
And I figured that parenting
them the way we, best we could.

00:21:11.250 --> 00:21:12.550
With a lot of love.

00:21:12.550 --> 00:21:14.280
And was going to be more important.

00:21:14.280 --> 00:21:18.220
Than a lot of activities I
might otherwise have done.

00:21:18.220 --> 00:21:19.520
And the other thing.

00:21:19.520 --> 00:21:22.910
And this is, I write about
this at length, in this book.

00:21:22.910 --> 00:21:26.860 position:56%
As the woman, you do have to let go.

00:21:26.860 --> 00:21:29.330
Right? My husband was
willing to be lead parent.

00:21:29.330 --> 00:21:31.800
But at some point, he said to me.

00:21:31.800 --> 00:21:33.250
"I'm doing this.

00:21:33.250 --> 00:21:35.840
But I'm doing this my way.

00:21:35.840 --> 00:21:39.130
You are not micromanaging
how I parent.

00:21:39.130 --> 00:21:41.230
If you want to do that,
you come home."

00:21:41.230 --> 00:21:44.110
Right? And he does things
very differently than I do.

00:21:44.110 --> 00:21:46.340
I always say, you know,
I'd come home and want them

00:21:46.340 --> 00:21:47.850
to clean their rooms and all this.

00:21:47.850 --> 00:21:50.530
And he would spend the weekend
showing them all the Marx

00:21:50.530 --> 00:21:51.830
Brothers movies.

00:21:51.830 --> 00:21:53.130
Like --

00:21:53.130 --> 00:21:54.430
[ Laughter ]

00:21:54.430 --> 00:21:59.400
-- And I came to realize, you know,
you really, you do have to assume.

00:21:59.400 --> 00:22:03.720
That a man is as capable
at home, and as a parent.

00:22:03.720 --> 00:22:06.020
As you are in the office.

00:22:06.020 --> 00:22:08.980
He is going to do it
differently, often.

00:22:08.980 --> 00:22:11.020
And, you know, everybody's
personalities differ.

00:22:11.020 --> 00:22:13.420
Sometimes the man is the neat
nick, and the woman isn't.

00:22:13.420 --> 00:22:16.040
I mean, it's not -- there
are many differences.

00:22:16.040 --> 00:22:19.650
But in the office, even though I do
something differently than a man.

00:22:19.650 --> 00:22:21.580
I assume I know what I'm doing.

00:22:21.580 --> 00:22:25.540
And I had to come to accept that
although I thought I knew better.

00:22:25.540 --> 00:22:26.840
Because my mother raised me.

00:22:26.840 --> 00:22:28.140
And her mother raised her.

00:22:28.140 --> 00:22:29.720
And her mother raised her.

00:22:29.720 --> 00:22:32.310
Who is to say I knew better?

00:22:32.310 --> 00:22:35.840
And he certainly thinks
he knows what he's doing.

00:22:35.840 --> 00:22:37.140
And I had to let go.

00:22:37.140 --> 00:22:39.360
And so that -- and
balls got dropped.

00:22:39.360 --> 00:22:42.410
Things that I thought needed
to be done were not done.

00:22:42.410 --> 00:22:45.820
But things that he thought
were important did get done.

00:22:45.820 --> 00:22:47.570
And as I look at our sons now.

00:22:47.570 --> 00:22:49.760
I think probably knowing
the Marx Brothers movies.

00:22:49.760 --> 00:22:51.490
Is more important than
whatever it was.

00:22:51.490 --> 00:22:52.790
&gt;&gt; Mary Louise Kelly: Than
